You probably need sudo?
It is likely that you will run into more issues, as we saw some changes into numpy has broken some old versions of TF.

On MacOS, we recommend using a CPU version, or you can always use a GPU supported TF through cloud instances that have GPUs.

body:
You probably need `sudo`?
It is likely that you will run into more issues, as we saw some changes into numpy has broken some old versions of TF.

On MacOS, we recommend using a CPU version, or you can always use a GPU supported TF through cloud instances that have GPUs.
